<HL>
   Business Brief -- Engelhard Corp.:
   Unit That Checks Radiation
   Is Sold to French Concern
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EC F.STG
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)
</IN>
<LP>
   Engelhard Corp. sold for cash a business that supplies
crystals and electronic systems that monitor levels of
exposure to radiation.
   The buyer is a subsidiary of the Paris glass manufacturer
Saint-Gobain S.A. Terms weren't disclosed; Engelhard had said
in February that it wanted to sell the business as part of a
restructuring.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Engelhard, of Edison, N.J., provides specialty chemical
products, engineered materials and precious-metals management
services.
</TEXT>
